Privacy Policy for Faceless

Last Updated: 9th of February 2025

This Privacy Policy describes how Faceless (the Bot/Application) collects, uses, and protects your data when you use our services. By using Faceless, you agree to the terms outlined in this policy.

1. Data We Collect
Faceless may collect the following information when you interact with the bot
- Username
- Display name
- Profile picture
- Messages
- Potentially email (if applicable)

2. How We Use Your Data
We use the collected data for the following purposes
- To provide bot functionalities such as processing commands and returning messages
- To improve the user experience and troubleshoot issues
- To ensure compliance with our Terms of Service

3. Data Sharing
We do not sell or share your personal data with third-party companies. Your data is used only for the intended purpose of running the botâ€™s services.

4. Data Storage and Security
Faceless takes appropriate measures to protect your data. However, we cannot guarantee complete security due to the nature of online services. Use the bot at your own risk.

5. Account Management
We do not manage Discord accounts. All account creation, suspension, or termination is handled by Discord. We are not responsible for any actions taken by Discord regarding your account.

6. User Rights
You have the right to request the deletion of your data collected by Faceless. To request data deletion, please contact us via our X (formerly Twitter) account @jaymakesmone.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy at any time. Continued use of Faceless after changes to this policy indicates your acceptance of the updated terms.

For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, contact us at @jaymakesmone on X.

